news.title: SAA expands its Pune footprint with over ₹2,700 crore residential mandates
news.para: SAA, an innovative force in real estate strategy and marketing, is gearing up for remarkable growth in Pune. With a portfolio of residential projects totaling around INR 2700 crore set for the upcoming financial year, this comes on the heels of a robust two-year journey in the city.

news.title: Nashik civic body intensifies property tax recovery drive for 2025-26 target
news.para: Nashik Municipal Corporation is intensifying property tax recovery to meet its Rs 275 crore target for 2025-26, with Rs 63 crore still outstanding. Following a successful amnesty scheme that collected Rs 66 crore, the civic body will issue fresh notices to defaulters. This push aims to recover current dues and a significant backlog of Rs 500 crore.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government proposes to revise land market values in urban areas from Feb 1
news.para: Andhra Pradesh government plans to revise urban land market values from February 1st to align with actual transaction prices and boost state revenue. This move, aimed at preventing revenue leakage, has raised concerns among real estate stakeholders about increased costs and potential dampening of buyer sentiment.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board plans to auction land parcels
news.para: Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB) is considering auctioning land parcels to private developers, a move away from its affordable housing mandate. This proposal, discussed by senior officials, has sparked debate about the board's relevance. Critics argue CHB has failed to provide affordable housing for the middle class, citing a lack of successful public schemes and stalled development plans.

news.title: Haryana regularises 26 colonies, none from Panchkula
news.para: Haryana government regularized 26 colonies statewide this month, but Panchkula district was notably excluded, despite prior BJP promises. This leaves numerous settlements in Pinjore-Kalka and Panchkula city awaiting regularization, with residents facing poor living conditions and lack of basic amenities.

news.title: HC stays Manesar civic body's demolition order for Ultratech Cement's plant
news.para: The Punjab and Haryana High Court has halted an order by Manesar Municipal Corporation to close Ultratech Cement's ready-mix concrete plant. The company had been operating for over two decades with all necessary approvals. The court has asked the corporation to file a reply by February 25. The plant's operations will continue until the next hearing.

news.title: Gujarat government likely to deregulate NA in town planning schemes
news.para: Gujarat government is considering removing the mandatory requirement for non-agriculture (NA) certificates in areas covered by town planning schemes. This move aims to streamline project approvals for residential, commercial, and industrial developments, addressing significant delays and potential corruption associated with the current process.

news.title: Income-tax search on Ahmedabad builders enters third day
news.para: Income tax officials continued their three-day search on two Ahmedabad real estate groups, targeting over 30 locations including corporate offices and residences. The operation, triggered by decoy buyers confirming cash transactions, has reportedly unearthed crores in undeclared business. Documents, digital data, and details of bank accounts and lockers are being scrutinized.

news.title: Techie's death: NGT flags waterlogging in trench, seeks reply from Noida authority
news.para: The National Green Tribunal is delving into the unfortunate accident involving a software engineer in Noida, who lost his life after his vehicle fell into an overly saturated trench. Investigators are looking into potential negligence by the Noida Authority regarding stormwater management, with evidence of years' worth of accumulated water creating hazardous conditions.

news.title: Noida techie death: Two more builders arrested
news.para: The Noida police have taken two builders into custody linked to the tragic drowning of a software engineer, whose car plunged into a water-filled trench adjacent to a construction site. The arrests reflect serious negligence at the Lotus Greens site, as a special investigation team delves into the incident, fueled by public outcry.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC issues stop work notices to 106 sites for not installing air quality monitoring system
news.para: The Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation has issued stop work orders to 106 construction projects for their failure to set up required air quality monitoring systems. This action targets various private and SRA initiatives that do not comply with regulations.

news.title: Non-compliance of orders, hurdles in completion of Unitech projects won't be tolerated: SC
news.para: The Supreme Court is addressing the significant delays caused by state authorities in the Unitech Ltd housing projects. The court has issued a stern warning to those resisting compliance with its directives. To expedite proceedings, it is implementing a prioritized hearing schedule.

news.title: RMZ to invest up to $30 billion in Mumbai region over next 10 years
news.para: RMZ has partnered with MMRDA and CIDCO. This collaboration will bring up to USD 30 billion in investments to the Mumbai Metropolitan Region. The initiative is planned over the next ten years. The company will lead investment structuring and development.

news.title: TVS Emerald raises ₹425 crore equity from IFC for new housing projects
news.para: TVS Emerald has secured Rs 425 crore in equity funding from the International Finance Corporation. This investment will fuel the development of two upcoming residential projects in Chennai and Bengaluru. These projects, set to launch next fiscal, have a combined revenue potential of Rs 4,400 crore.

news.title: We need a housing revolution: Niranjan Hiranandani, chairman, Naredco
news.para: Naredco has urged the government to lower income tax rates for individuals and partnerships.   Proposals include increasing home loan interest deductions and reinstating the Income Tax Settlement Commission.  These measures aim to revive the sector and address housing shortages ahead of the Union Budget 2026.

news.title: Survey of land under NAKSHA starts in Tiswadi
news.para: Land surveys have begun in select Tiswadi taluka areas under the NAKSHA programme, covering Panaji localities like Caranzalem and St Inez, along with Bambolim and Taleigao. Residents are urged to cooperate with survey teams for accurate property mapping. Property owners, including those abroad or renting out, must ensure their rights are correctly recorded during this 10-15 day per zone process.

news.title: PropertyPistol raises ₹25 crore in pre-series B funding
news.para: PropertyPistol has successfully garnered ₹25 crore in a pre-series B financing round, headed by the proficient Ashish Kacholia alongside support from previous investors. This injection of capital is set to accelerate the company’s expansion into Dubai and optimize its distribution channels.

news.title: ASF Insignia raises ₹1,250 crore capital commitment from Alpha Alternatives
news.para: ASF Insignia has landed an investment of around ₹1,250 crore from Alpha Alternatives, earmarked for a state-of-the-art integrated commercial IT office project in Gurugram.

news.title: DLF's net profit up 13.66% in Q3 FY26
news.para: DLF's net profit saw an increase of 13.66 percent for the quarter ending December 31, 2025. Total income also grew by 42.71 percent. The company's gross collections reached ₹5,100 crore for the quarter.

news.title: Bengaluru development body reclaims encroached land worth over ₹700 crore in 14 demolition drives
news.para: The Bangalore Development Authority (BDA) conducted 14 demolition drives between July and December last year, reclaiming over 25 acres of encroached land valued at more than Rs 704.3 crore. These drives targeted unauthorized structures on land acquired for BDA projects, with significant recoveries in JP Nagar 9th Phase. The reclaimed land will be utilized for future BDA projects or auctioned.
